# Armada project

## Required workflow

1. **Read `ARMADA_DESIGN_SYSTEM.md`** at the repo root before writing or editing any component, page, or CSS.
2. **Never hardcode** hex colors, raw `px` spacing/sizing, or font sizes — use CSS custom properties from `src/styles/tokens.css`.
3. **Verify token names** in `src/styles/tokens.css` before using any `var(--…)` (semantic and primitive names must exist).
4. **Run `npm run build`** before marking any task complete (catches `tsc` errors Vercel will reject).

Exceptions: rare cases called out in the design system (e.g. gradient overlays on media). When in doubt, check the doc and tokens first.

## Single source of truth

- **Only work in this folder:** `armada-crowdfund` (git + GitHub + Vercel).
- Do **not** edit `armada-v2` — it is an old duplicate and is out of date (e.g. centered header nav).
- Run `npm run dev` here only → `http://localhost:5173/`

## Build & deploy

- Production build: `npm run build` → `tsc && vite build`.
- `npm run dev` does not run `tsc`.
- New HTML entries: `*.html`, `main-*.tsx`, `vite.config.ts`, and `vercel.json` route if needed.
- Do not commit unless the user asks.

## Styling

- CSS Modules per component (`Component.module.css`).
- Prefer semantic tokens (`--semantic-*`); use primitives (`--primitives-*`) when semantic aliases do not exist.
- Flow shell zone gaps: `--primitives-spacing-11` (44px).
- Prefer minimal, focused diffs; match existing naming and patterns.

## Participate flows

- **Path 1** — `ParticipateFlowInviteLink` on `InviteLanding` (`/invite`): inline 480×500, progress **Connect → Commit → Review → Confirm** (`INVITE_LINK_STEPS`).
- **Path 2** — `ParticipateFlowCrowdfund` in `CrowdfundExperience`: modal, progress **Commit → Review → Confirm** (`CROWDFUND_MODAL_STEPS`).
- Step screens live in `ParticipateFlow/screens/`; Step 0 in `ParticipateFlow/steps/Step0Invite/`.
- Do not bundle steps into one file; extend the correct orchestrator.

## Step 0 invite card

- Grid stack (`grid-area: stack`) for video, overlay, content.
- Overlay gradient: black 20% top → 80% bottom (see design system).
- `variant="landing"` on Path 1; `hideConnectEyebrow` when wallet already connected in modal.

## Confirmation (Step 5)

- **View your position** when `onViewPosition` is set and (`showViewPositionButton` or `isAdditionalCommit`).
- Path 1: use `showViewPositionButton` for first commit.
- Path 2: additional commit only for secondary button; first commit uses modal X → My Position.

## Header & session

- **Header** — `activeNav="project" | "crowdfund" | "myposition"`, not `navItems`. Showcase demos use `<NavBar items={...} />`.
- Connected wallet: `WalletPillMenu` (copy, disconnect).
- **Demo session** — `DemoSessionProvider` + `sessionStorage`; separate Vite entries do not share in-memory React state.

## Components (patterns)

**Steps** — `status`: `default` | `error` | `confirmed`. Errors at connect and confirmation as appropriate per flow.

**JoinButton** — `expanded` for parent hover; `size="lg"` on invite landing Step 0.

**Hop colors** — import from `src/constants/graphHopColors.ts`, do not duplicate hex.

**Allowlist** — address-based (`participateFlowWallets.ts`); use `Step1WalletNotWhitelisted` for blocked addresses.
